# Asana Workflow Rules

## When developer asks "what to work on?"

1. Show Review / Test tasks first (awaiting deploy/testing)
2. Show TODO tasks (taken into work, not started)
3. Show In Progress tasks for current user
4. Ask what to pick

## Task lifecycle

- `start <id>` — auto-assign to current user, move to In Progress
- `done <id>` — mark completed, move to Done

## Priorities

- Bugs > Review/Test > TODO > Backlog

## Limits

- Max 2 tasks In Progress per person
- Before taking a new task — finish or return current ones

## Naming

- Always use prefix: `[Backend] Task name`
- Available prefixes are defined in asana.json
